VALUES
(44, 15, 1, 48, 5, 6, 6, 'Except ye be circumcised after the manner of Moses', 'Circumcision and Faith Connection', 'This connection highlights the debate over circumcision as a requirement for salvation. Both passages emphasize that faith, rather than circumcision, is what truly matters in Christ.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 1, 44, 15, 5, 5, 'ye cannot be saved', 'Circumcision and Salvation Debate', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of circumcision for salvation. They reflect the ongoing debate among early believers regarding adherence to the law of Moses.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 1, 3, 12, 3, 3, 'be circumcised after the manner of Moses', 'Connection of Circumcision Requirements', 'This connection highlights the requirement of circumcision in both passages. Acts 15:1 discusses the necessity of circumcision for salvation, while Leviticus 12:3 specifies the act of circumcision on the eighth day.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 1, 51, 2, 8, 8, 'ye cannot be saved', 'Connection of Legalism and Deceit', 'This connection highlights the warning against legalistic teachings that can lead believers away from Christ. Both passages emphasize the danger of adhering to human traditions and rules, which can undermine true faith and salvation.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 1, 45, 4, 8, 12, 'ye cannot be saved', 'Circumcision and Righteousness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between circumcision and faith. Acts 15:1 presents the requirement of circumcision for salvation, while Romans 4:8-12 argues that righteousness is granted through faith, independent of circumcision.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 1, 46, 7, 18, 19, 'ye cannot be saved', 'Circumcision and Salvation Debate', 'This connection highlights the debate over circumcision and its relevance to salvation. Both passages emphasize the idea that circumcision is not necessary for salvation, focusing instead on the importance of keeping God''s commandments.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 1, 48, 2, 11, 14, 'Except ye be circumcised after the manner of Moses', 'Circumcision and Gentile Relations', 'Both passages emphasize the issue of circumcision and its implications for salvation and fellowship among Jews and Gentiles. Acts 15:1 introduces the requirement of circumcision for salvation, while Galatians 2:11-14 illustrates the tension it creates in Peter''s behavior towards Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 2, 44, 15, 22, 23, 'Paul and Barnabas, and certain other of them, should go up to Jerusalem', 'Council Decision and Communication', 'This connection highlights the decision made by Paul and Barnabas to go to Jerusalem, which leads to the apostles and elders sending chosen men back to Antioch. Both passages emphasize the involvement of the apostles and elders in addressing the question of the Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 2, 44, 15, 6, 7, 'no small dissension and disputation', 'Disputation and Decision-Making', 'This connection highlights the theme of disputation as both passages describe significant discussions among the apostles regarding the inclusion of Gentiles. The phrase ''much disputing'' in the target passage reflects the earlier ''no small dissension and disputation'' in the source, emphasizing the seriousness of the matter at hand.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 2, 48, 2, 1, 2, 'go up to Jerusalem', 'Journey to Jerusalem', 'Both passages emphasize a journey to Jerusalem where important discussions about the gospel took place. Acts 15:2 describes the decision to go to Jerusalem, while Galatians 2:1-2 recounts Paul''s visit to communicate the gospel he preaches.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 2, 47, 11, 5, 5, 'no small dissension and disputation', 'Apostolic Authority and Disputes', 'This connection highlights the theme of apostolic authority and the disputes surrounding it. In Acts, Paul and Barnabas engage in significant debate regarding doctrine, while in 2 Corinthians, Paul asserts his standing among the apostles.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 2, 48, 1, 6, 10, NULL, 'Gospel Integrity and Disputes', 'This connection highlights the concern over maintaining the true gospel. Both passages emphasize the importance of not being removed from the original message and the consequences of preaching a different gospel.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 2, 2, 18, 23, 23, NULL, 'Leadership and Guidance in Conflict', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking guidance in times of dispute. Both passages emphasize the importance of consulting leaders to ensure peace and order among the people.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 2, 9, 8, 7, 7, NULL, 'Rejection of Authority Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of rejection of authority. In Acts, the dispute arises over the acceptance of new practices, paralleling the rejection of God''s reign in 1 Samuel.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 3, 44, 14, 27, 27, 'declaring the conversion of the Gentiles', 'Joy in Gentile Conversion', 'Both passages emphasize the conversion of the Gentiles and the resulting joy within the church. Acts 15:3 mentions the joy caused by declaring the conversion, while Acts 14:27 highlights how God opened the door of faith to the Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 3, 44, 21, 5, 5, 'brought on their way by the church', 'Journey and Community Support', 'Both passages emphasize the communal aspect of travel and support within the church. In Acts 15:3, the church brings Paul and Barnabas on their way, while in Acts 21:5, the community accompanies the travelers, highlighting the joy and unity among believers.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 3, 45, 15, 24, 24, 'being brought on their way', 'Journey and Support in Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of being ''brought on their way'' by the church, highlighting the communal support in ministry journeys. This connection illustrates the importance of fellowship and encouragement among believers as they undertake missions.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 3, 46, 16, 6, 6, NULL, 'Journey and Community Support', 'This connection highlights the theme of communal support in the journeys of early Christians. Both passages emphasize the idea of being brought on a journey by the community, reflecting the importance of fellowship in their missions.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 3, 56, 3, 13, 13, NULL, 'Journey and Support of Messengers', 'This connection highlights the theme of supporting and sending messengers on their journeys. Both passages emphasize the importance of providing for those who spread the message, fostering joy and diligence in their missions.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 3, 23, 60, 4, 5, 'conversion of the Gentiles', 'Connection of Gentile Conversion', 'This connection highlights the theme of Gentile inclusion in God''s plan. Both passages emphasize the gathering of the Gentiles and the joy that accompanies their conversion.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 3, 23, 66, 12, 14, 'great joy unto all the brethren', 'Joy in Gentile Conversion', 'This connection highlights the theme of joy associated with the inclusion of the Gentiles in God''s plan. Both passages emphasize the rejoicing that comes from God''s blessings extended to the Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 4, 44, 14, 27, 27, NULL, 'Connection of God''s Actions', 'Both passages emphasize the declaration of what God had done. They highlight the role of the church in sharing the message of faith, particularly regarding the Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 4, 44, 15, 12, 12, 'all things that God had done with them', 'Connection of God''s Works', 'Both passages emphasize the declaration of what God has done through Paul and Barnabas. They highlight the miracles and wonders performed among the Gentiles, showcasing the divine activity in their ministry.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 4, 45, 15, 18, 18, 'all things that God had done with them', 'Connection of Divine Action', 'Both passages emphasize the actions of God and Christ in relation to the Gentiles. Acts 15:4 speaks of what God has done, while Romans 15:18 refers to what Christ has wrought through Paul to make the Gentiles obedient.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 4, 40, 10, 40, 40, 'received of the church', 'Reception and Divine Mission', 'This connection highlights the theme of reception in both passages. In Acts, the church receives the apostles, paralleling how receiving the apostles in Matthew signifies receiving Jesus and God.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 4, 45, 15, 7, 7, 'received of the church', 'Receiving One Another in Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of acceptance within the community of believers. Both passages emphasize the importance of being received by one another, reflecting the acceptance shown by Christ.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 4, 46, 15, 10, 10, 'all things that God had done', 'Grace and Labor in Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the role of God''s grace in the lives of believers. Acts 15:4 highlights the work God did through the apostles, while 1 Corinthians 15:10 reflects on how grace enabled Paul to labor abundantly.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 4, 47, 5, 19, 19, 'all things that God had done', 'Reconciliation Theme in Scripture', 'This connection highlights the theme of God actively working to reconcile humanity to Himself. In Acts, the declaration of what God has done reflects His reconciling work mentioned in 2 Corinthians.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 5, 48, 5, 1, 3, 'to command them to keep the law of Moses', 'Connection of Law and Circumcision', 'Both passages emphasize the issue of circumcision and the law of Moses. Acts 15:5 discusses the necessity of circumcision, while Galatians 5:1-3 warns against it, highlighting the tension between law and freedom in Christ.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 5, 44, 15, 1, 1, NULL, 'Circumcision and Salvation Debate', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of circumcision for salvation according to the law of Moses. This connection highlights the early church''s struggle with the requirements for Gentile believers.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 5, 50, 3, 5, 8, 'to circumcise them, and to command them to keep the law of Moses', 'Connection of Circumcision and Law', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of circumcision and adherence to the law. Acts 15:5 discusses the necessity of circumcision and the law of Moses, while Philippians 3:5-8 reflects on the speaker''s past as a Pharisee who strictly followed the law.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 5, 44, 15, 24, 24, NULL, 'Circumcision and the Law of Moses', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of circumcision and keeping the law of Moses. The first passage introduces the debate, while the second passage addresses the confusion caused by those advocating for these requirements.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 5, 44, 21, 20, 20, 'to keep the law of Moses', 'Connection of Jewish Belief and Law', 'This connection highlights the ongoing tension between Jewish believers'' zeal for the law and the debate over its requirements for Gentile converts. Both passages emphasize the significance of the law of Moses in the early church.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 5, 44, 24, 5, 5, 'sect of the Pharisees', 'Connection of Sect and Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of sects within Judaism. The Pharisees in Acts 15:5 represent a specific belief system, while the Nazarenes in Acts 24:5 are identified as a sect that emerged from early Christianity.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 6, 20, 15, 22, 22, 'came together for to consider', 'Importance of Counsel in Decision-Making', 'This connection highlights the significance of gathering counsel in making decisions. Acts 15:6 shows the apostles and elders coming together, while Proverbs 15:22 emphasizes that purposes are established through a multitude of counselors.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 6, 44, 15, 25, 25, 'came together for to consider', 'Assembly of Apostles and Elders', 'This connection highlights the theme of unity among the apostles and elders as they come together to make important decisions. Both passages emphasize the collective agreement and purpose in their assembly.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 6, 58, 13, 7, 7, NULL, 'Leadership and Faithfulness', 'This connection highlights the role of leaders in the community. Both passages emphasize the importance of following those who have spoken the word of God and considering their faith.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 6, 58, 13, 17, 17, 'the apostles and elders came together', 'Leadership and Accountability in the Church', 'This connection highlights the importance of church leadership as seen in both passages. Acts 15:6 discusses the gathering of apostles and elders to make decisions, while Hebrews 13:17 emphasizes obedience to those in authority who watch over the souls of the congregation.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 6, 44, 6, 2, 2, 'came together for to consider', 'Gathering for Decision Making', 'This connection highlights the communal decision-making process in the early church. Both passages emphasize the importance of gathering leaders to address significant matters, whether it be the distribution of resources or doctrinal issues.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 6, 40, 18, 20, 20, NULL, 'Gathering in Christ''s Name', 'This connection highlights the importance of gathering together. Both passages emphasize the communal aspect of faith, where believers come together, and Christ''s presence is assured among them.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 7, 45, 10, 17, 18, 'hear the word of the gospel', 'Connection of Hearing and Faith', 'This connection highlights the importance of hearing the gospel for faith to arise. Both passages emphasize that the message of God reaches all people, leading to belief.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 7, 48, 2, 7, 9, 'that the Gentiles by my mouth should hear', 'Gospel to Gentiles Connection', 'This connection highlights the shared mission of Peter and Paul in spreading the gospel to the Gentiles. Both passages emphasize the divine choice and empowerment for this task, illustrating the unity in their apostolic missions.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 7, 13, 28, 4, 5, 'God made choice among us', 'Divine Choice and Leadership', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine selection in leadership roles. Both passages emphasize how God chooses individuals for significant purposes, with Peter chosen to share the gospel and David chosen to establish a kingly lineage.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 7, 44, 15, 2, 2, 'much disputing', 'Disputation and Decision in Jerusalem', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of disputation among the early church leaders regarding the inclusion of Gentiles. Acts 15:2 describes the initial disagreement that led to a council in Jerusalem, while Acts 15:7 shows Peter affirming God''s choice in this matter.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 7, 44, 10, 20, 20, 'the Gentiles by my mouth should hear', 'Connection of Gentile Inclusion', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s directive to reach the Gentiles. In Acts 15:7, Peter refers to God''s choice for the Gentiles to hear the gospel, which aligns with the command in Acts 10:20 to go without doubt to the Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 7, 2, 4, 12, 12, 'by my mouth should hear', 'Divine Guidance in Speech', 'This connection highlights God''s promise to guide speech in both passages. Peter refers to God''s choice in speaking to the Gentiles, while Exodus emphasizes God''s assurance to Moses about what to say.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 7, 24, 1, 9, 9, NULL, 'Divine Communication to Humanity', 'This connection highlights the theme of God placing His words in the mouths of His chosen messengers. In both passages, Peter and Jeremiah are depicted as instruments through whom God communicates His message to others.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 8, 44, 1, 24, 24, 'which knoweth the hearts', 'Connection of Divine Knowledge', 'Both passages emphasize God''s knowledge of hearts, highlighting His role in discerning choices and granting the Holy Spirit. This connection underscores the divine authority in guiding decisions and affirming faith.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 8, 44, 10, 47, 47, NULL, 'Connection of Holy Ghost Reception', 'Both passages emphasize the reception of the Holy Ghost by believers. Acts 15:8 mentions God giving the Holy Ghost, while Acts 10:47 refers to those who have received the Holy Ghost, highlighting a shared experience among believers.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 8, 58, 4, 13, 13, 'knoweth the hearts', 'Divine Knowledge of Hearts', 'Both passages emphasize God''s omniscience and ability to see into the hearts of individuals. Acts 15:8 highlights God''s knowledge of hearts in granting the Holy Spirit, while Hebrews 4:13 states that all things are naked and opened to His sight.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 8, 66, 2, 23, 23, NULL, 'Connection of Heart Knowledge', 'This connection highlights God''s knowledge of hearts in both passages. Acts emphasizes God''s witness to hearts, while Revelation asserts that He searches hearts and rewards according to works.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 8, 9, 16, 7, 7, NULL, 'God''s Insight into Hearts', 'Both passages emphasize God''s ability to see the heart rather than outward appearances. Acts 15:8 highlights God''s knowledge of hearts, while 1 Samuel 16:7 contrasts human judgment with divine insight.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 8, 11, 8, 39, 39, NULL, 'Connection of Divine Knowledge', 'Both passages emphasize God''s knowledge of human hearts. Acts 15:8 highlights God''s witness to hearts, while 1 Kings 8:39 states that God knows the hearts of all men.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 8, 13, 28, 9, 9, 'God, which knoweth the hearts', 'Connection of Heart and Understanding', 'Both passages emphasize God''s knowledge of hearts. Acts 15:8 states God knows hearts, while 1 Chronicles 28:9 mentions the Lord searching all hearts.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 9, 49, 3, 6, 6, 'purifying their hearts by faith', 'Unity of Believers in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the inclusion of Gentiles in the faith community. Acts 15:9 speaks of purifying hearts by faith, while Ephesians 3:6 highlights Gentiles as fellow heirs and partakers of the promise.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 9, 48, 5, 6, 6, 'purifying their hearts by faith', 'Faith and Purification Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of faith in Jesus Christ for all believers, regardless of their background. Acts 15:9 speaks of purifying hearts by faith, while Galatians 5:6 highlights that faith works through love, indicating a shared theme of faith''s transformative power.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 9, 44, 10, 28, 28, 'purifying their hearts by faith', 'Purification and Acceptance of All', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of God purifying hearts and not calling any person unclean. This connection highlights the inclusion of Gentiles in the faith community, demonstrating that faith transcends ethnic boundaries.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 9, 45, 3, 22, 22, NULL, 'Unity in Faith', 'Both passages emphasize that there is no difference between believers, highlighting the universal nature of faith in purifying hearts and granting righteousness. This connection underscores the inclusivity of faith for all who believe.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 9, 44, 11, 12, 12, 'purifying their hearts by faith', 'Purification and Acceptance', 'Both passages emphasize the inclusion of Gentiles in the faith community. Acts 15:9 speaks of purifying hearts by faith, while Acts 11:12 describes the acceptance of Gentiles without doubt.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 9, 46, 1, 2, 2, 'purifying their hearts by faith', 'Purification and Sanctification Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of purification and sanctification through faith in Christ. Acts 15:9 speaks of purifying hearts by faith, while 1 Corinthians 1:2 refers to being sanctified in Christ Jesus.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 9, 48, 3, 28, 28, 'purifying their hearts by faith', 'Unity in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the removal of distinctions among believers, highlighting that all are unified in faith. Acts 15:9 speaks of purifying hearts by faith, while Galatians 3:28 declares that all are one in Christ Jesus.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 10, 40, 23, 4, 4, 'yoke upon the neck of the disciples', 'Burden of the Law', 'Both passages emphasize the imposition of heavy burdens on individuals. Acts 15:10 speaks of a yoke that is unmanageable, while Matthew 23:4 describes burdens laid on shoulders that are grievous to bear.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 10, 48, 5, 1, 1, 'yoke upon the neck of the disciples', 'Yoke of Bondage and Freedom', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of a ''yoke'' that burdens believers. Acts 15:10 warns against placing a yoke on disciples, while Galatians 5:1 encourages standing firm in the freedom from such bondage.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 10, 48, 4, 9, 9, 'yoke upon the neck of the disciples', 'Bondage and Yoke Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of bondage and the burdensome nature of the law. Acts 15:10 speaks of a ''yoke'' that is difficult to bear, while Galatians 4:9 refers to ''weak and beggarly elements'' that lead to bondage.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 10, 58, 9, 9, 9, 'yoke upon the neck of the disciples', 'Burden of the Law', 'This connection highlights the theme of burdensome religious practices. Both passages emphasize that the yoke of the law and the sacrifices offered were inadequate for achieving true spiritual perfection.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 10, 23, 7, 12, 12, 'tempt ye God', 'Tempting the Lord Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the act of tempting God. In Acts, it warns against putting a burden on disciples, while Isaiah shows Ahaz''s refusal to tempt the Lord.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 10, 40, 4, 7, 7, 'tempt ye God', 'Tempting God Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of tempting God. Both passages address the idea of not putting God to the test, emphasizing the seriousness of such actions.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 10, 2, 17, 2, 2, 'tempt ye God', 'Tempting God and His People', 'Both passages emphasize the act of tempting God. In Acts, the yoke represents a burden that is being imposed, paralleling the people''s challenge to Moses in Exodus, where they question God''s provision.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 11, 45, 3, 24, 24, 'through the grace of the Lord Jesus Christ', 'Connection of Grace and Salvation', 'Both passages emphasize salvation through grace. Acts 15:11 speaks of being saved through grace, while Romans 3:24 highlights justification by grace, linking the two concepts.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 11, 56, 3, 4, 7, 'through the grace of the Lord Jesus Christ', 'Salvation by Grace Connection', 'Both passages emphasize salvation through grace rather than works. Acts 15:11 states salvation is through the grace of the Lord Jesus Christ, while Titus 3:5 highlights that salvation is not by works but according to God''s mercy.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 11, 49, 2, 5, 9, 'through the grace of the Lord Jesus Christ', 'Salvation by Grace Connection', 'Both passages emphasize salvation through grace, highlighting that it is not based on human effort. Acts 15:11 states salvation is through the grace of the Lord Jesus Christ, while Ephesians 2:5-9 elaborates that salvation is a gift of God, not of works.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 11, 56, 2, 11, 11, 'grace of the Lord Jesus Christ', 'Connection of Grace and Salvation', 'Both passages emphasize the role of grace in salvation. Acts 15:11 highlights salvation through grace, while Titus 2:11 states that grace brings salvation to all men.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 11, 48, 2, 16, 16, 'we believe that through the grace', 'Salvation through Faith', 'Both passages emphasize salvation through faith rather than works. Acts 15:11 highlights salvation through grace, while Galatians 2:16 stresses justification by faith in Jesus Christ.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 11, 45, 6, 23, 23, 'through the grace of the Lord Jesus Christ', 'Salvation through Grace and Gift', 'Both passages emphasize salvation and eternal life as gifts from God. Acts 15:11 highlights salvation through grace, while Romans 6:23 contrasts the wages of sin with the gift of God, linking grace and eternal life.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 11, 47, 13, 14, 14, 'the grace of the Lord Jesus Christ', 'Connection of Grace in Salvation', 'Both passages emphasize the grace of the Lord Jesus Christ as central to the believer''s experience. Acts 15:11 highlights salvation through grace, while 2 Corinthians 13:14 invokes grace as a blessing for the community.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 12, 44, 14, 27, 27, 'Gentiles', 'Connection of Gentile Mission', 'Both passages emphasize God''s work among the Gentiles. Acts 15:12 mentions miracles and wonders, while Acts 14:27 highlights the opening of faith to them.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 12, 44, 15, 4, 4, NULL, 'Connection of Divine Works', 'Both passages emphasize the acts of God through Paul and Barnabas. They highlight the declaration of what God had done among the Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 15, 12, 43, 4, 48, 48, 'miracles and wonders', 'Connection of Signs and Wonders', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of miracles and wonders in fostering belief. Acts 15:12 highlights the miracles performed by Barnabas and Paul among the Gentiles, while John 4:48 suggests that belief often requires witnessing such signs.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
